Name: BE-4 Engine
des: The first ox-rich staged combustion engine made in the U.S. will power the next generation of American orbital rockets.

Name: BE-3 Engine
des: The BE-3 is the first new liquid hydrogen-fueled rocket engine to be developed for production in America in over a decade.

Name: BE-7 Engine
des: BE-7 is an additively manufactured, high-performance, dual-expander cycle engine, generating 40 kN (10,000 lbf) thrust.
